703812f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cooper Street - Central Avenue
703812f-a.text:
149-159 Cooper Street, at and north of Central Ave. The corner house
(149), was at one time occupied by one Hatfield, who used it as a residence
and also for the manufacture of ''fire-works''. It was later used as a saloon.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Colk ction.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
